Like everyone else that had come before her, Mary needed saving.

22:14.439 --> 22:24.690
She was a sinner, just like us, in need of the grace of God, and she rejoiced that God saw her and her need for him.

22:26.402 --> 22:27.864
finally Mary trusted him.

22:28.545 --> 22:34.495
And what God was gonna do in her future, Luke chapter one verse 38, I am the Lord's servant said Mary.

22:35.317 --> 22:37.260
May it be done to me according to your word.

22:37.300 --> 22:43.049
And in verse 45, blessed is she who has believed that the Lord would fulfill what he's spoken to her.

22:45.253 --> 22:53.426
You know, we often forget this, but for Mary to respond in faith to God's plan for her life would have meant that she was in for a difficult road.

22:54.690 --> 22:57.655
because Mary lived in an honor and shame culture.

22:59.257 --> 23:05.327
At the end of this passage, we see that Mary stayed with Elizabeth for three more months, and then she came back home.

23:06.168 --> 23:10.255
And when she came back home, three months pregnant, you know what people would have seen?

23:10.315 --> 23:12.258
They would have seen a baby bump.

23:13.840 --> 23:15.323
They would have seen her expecting.

23:16.545 --> 23:17.446
And you know what they would have done?

23:17.466 --> 23:18.367
They would have done the math.

23:19.690 --> 23:20.150
Wait a minute.

23:20.992 --> 23:22.514
Mary's not married.

23:24.162 --> 23:25.003
What's going on here?

23:25.924 --> 23:29.047
And that would have brought shame to her and Joseph.

23:30.369 --> 23:38.778
But Mary chose to trust God even though it meant that others may have judged her or thought ill or wrong of her.

23:40.940 --> 23:53.234
See, when we think about Christmas, the beginning of the greatest rescue story, how we are the ones God came to save, we should respond in the same ways

23:53.730 --> 23:57.916
that Mary responded regarding God's work in her life.

23:58.978 --> 24:05.667
We should respond with wonder and with rejoicing and with trust.

24:07.510 --> 24:10.995
Mary wondered at what God had done in her past.

24:11.656 --> 24:14.720
She reflected on God's grace to her and her people over the centuries.

24:15.722 --> 24:21.330
She rejoiced about what God was doing in her in the present that he picked her for his purposes.

24:22.594 --> 24:31.968
And finally, she trusted him for what was coming in the future, that he would continue to sustain her as she walked in faith in her community.

24:33.731 --> 24:43.425
You know, to wonder, it's to have that feeling of surprise and that feeling of admiration that comes from something beautiful and unexpected.

24:43.465 --> 24:47.952
And what God did for us, it is all of those things.

24:49.073 --> 24:52.178
It is beautiful and it's unexpected.

24:53.154 --> 24:54.235
and it's inexplicable.

24:55.416 --> 25:00.402
Because the rescue story, it didn't begin once humanity had gotten its act together.

25:02.044 --> 25:07.169
Or when the human race had finally improved enough for God to think, okay, now they're ready.

25:07.229 --> 25:10.353
No, it was the opposite.

25:11.454 --> 25:14.918
Jesus entered the world to rescue sinners.

25:16.539 --> 25:17.320
His enemies.

25:18.662 --> 25:22.546
We see the Apostle Paul describe this in Romans chapter five, verse eight,

25:23.554 --> 25:32.968
Look at what he writes, but God proves his own love for us in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

25:33.528 --> 25:44.184
Then verse 10, for if while we were enemies, we were reconciled to God through the death of his son, then how much more, having been reconciled, will we be saved by his life?

25:46.006 --> 25:47.448
That is a rescue story.

25:48.750 --> 25:51.314
A rescue we're coming to rescue enemies.

25:52.482 --> 25:58.110
Those who rejected Him, who spat on Him, who mocked Him.

25:58.170 --> 26:01.254
There's no rescue story like that.

26:02.976 --> 26:16.355
This truth leads us to wonder that as we were sinning, as we were living for ourselves, as we were walking further and further away from God, He pursued us.

26:17.857 --> 26:18.558
He came near.

26:20.220 --> 26:21.522
He made a way for us.

26:21.890 --> 26:30.460
to be reconciled back to Him, to experience this grace of God at first comes from seeing your need.

26:32.842 --> 26:39.770
You won't be rescued if you don't accept it, if you don't believe it that you need it.

26:43.835 --> 26:50.002
First, it comes from accepting and believing that yes, we are far from God and our sin.

26:51.106 --> 26:53.950
but that Jesus came near to reconcile us.

26:55.612 --> 27:06.025
If you've never chosen to follow Christ, choose to follow Him today, to believe and to wonder at this truth of what God has done for you.

27:07.727 --> 27:16.818
And if you've already done that, if you're here and you are a Christian, look at your life and wonder at God's grace to you.

27:18.210 --> 27:26.743
Answer this question, what has God done in your life in the past that just leads you to awe and admiration of who he is?

27:26.763 --> 27:32.852
Along with wonder, like Mary, our faith, it should lead us to rejoice.

27:33.973 --> 27:37.959
You know, the word joy is a word we see a lot around the Christmas season.

27:37.999 --> 27:38.780
We sing about it.

27:39.481 --> 27:42.786
We decorate our trees with ornaments that say joy on it.

27:42.806 --> 27:47.954
We see that word show up in the Christmas story and joy is a little bit different than just feeling happy.

27:49.090 --> 27:51.052
Because we all pursue happiness, right?

27:51.553 --> 27:53.635
And gladness and well-being.

27:53.655 --> 27:58.982
But joy is the deeper well in which that happiness should come from.

28:00.524 --> 28:03.307
Joy is a deep contentment of the soul.

28:05.350 --> 28:07.672
And it's something that God actually does in us.

28:08.513 --> 28:09.615
It's a fruit of the spirit.

28:10.696 --> 28:14.040
It's something that the spirit just grows in us as we walk in faith every day.

28:14.120 --> 28:16.042
We don't white knuckle joy.

28:17.364 --> 28:19.026
If someone tells you to be joyful,

28:19.298 --> 28:22.422
You don't often think, all right, you want to punch him, right?

28:23.263 --> 28:25.486
Because it's something that happens.

28:26.086 --> 28:31.773
God does it as we rest in his truth of who we are and what he's done.

28:31.813 --> 28:34.857
It's a result of what God is doing.

28:36.479 --> 28:38.682
See, Jesus talked about this in Luke 15.

28:38.782 --> 28:44.749
Jesus told all these parables in Luke 15 about lost things being found.

28:45.931 --> 28:48.434
In one of his stories, he said it was about this shepherd,

28:49.026 --> 28:50.949
who loses one of his 100 sheep.

28:52.691 --> 28:55.455
And he goes and he looks for the one.

28:55.555 --> 28:58.780
He leaves the 99 behind to find the one that's lost.

29:00.021 --> 29:01.283
And this is what Jesus said.

29:01.323 --> 29:05.008
This is his ending line from this parable, Luke 15, verse seven.

29:06.070 --> 29:17.746
I tell you, in the same way, there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over 99 righteous people who don't need repentance.

29:19.874 --> 29:38.782
Throughout the Gospels, we see over and over again that nothing compares to the joy of being known by God and knowing Him, not more money, not more stuff, not more relationships, nothing else compares.

29:40.425 --> 29:46.674
And as Jesus interacted with people, as He spoke to them, as He touched them,

29:48.162 --> 29:56.515
As He taught them, we see their lives change because they experience that deep contentment of the soul.

29:58.758 --> 30:03.586
Because they finally experience the rescue that Jesus came to accomplish.

30:05.689 --> 30:07.952
Think about your life right now.

30:09.655 --> 30:14.242
Where can you rejoice in what God is doing in your life today?

30:16.405 --> 30:16.946
Finally,

30:17.474 --> 30:24.564
When we remember that Jesus is the Savior that was sent into the world for us, that leads us to continue to trust in Him.

30:25.826 --> 30:28.991
Jesus Himself, at the end of His earthly life, He modeled this for us.

30:30.253 --> 30:34.158
If you remember, as He went to the cross, He was praying to His heavenly Father.

30:34.198 --> 30:40.407
He was about to take on the weight of our sin and experience separation from His heavenly Father for the first time.

30:40.848 --> 30:44.914
And He asked God, Abba, Father, is there another way?

30:46.050 --> 30:48.512
If there is, can you just take this cup from me?

30:49.894 --> 30:51.816
But that's not the last thing Jesus said.

30:51.836 --> 30:57.561
The last thing he said was not my will, but yours be done.

30:59.443 --> 31:10.654
Jesus trusted in God's plan for his life, how through his perfect life, his death on the cross and through his resurrection that people would have the opportunity to be rescued.

31:12.395 --> 31:15.058
Mary trusted in God's plan for her life.

31:15.682 --> 31:20.907
for the work and what he had put before her to be faithful in and to trust him in.

31:21.848 --> 31:34.661
Even though that meant hardship with her relationships, with her health, with her community, for Mary, it was worth it because she knew God was with her.

31:37.304 --> 31:43.570
Where do you in your life and whatever is next, where do you need to trust

31:43.906 --> 31:46.390
in God and in His plans for you for the future.

31:48.873 --> 32:01.632
See, as we think about the Christmas story, what God has done for us were led to these things, were led to wonder and to rejoice and to trust Him.

32:03.074 --> 32:05.737
I want to encourage you, think about those questions this week.

32:05.758 --> 32:08.722
Just where God has you, your past, your present, your future.

32:09.863 --> 32:11.666
What has God done in your life?

32:12.450 --> 32:15.213
that leads you to awe and wonder of who he is.

32:16.855 --> 32:20.280
Where can you rejoice in what God is doing in you today?

32:21.701 --> 32:25.286
And finally, where do you need to trust him for whatever's next?

32:27.208 --> 32:38.482
These questions, they remind us that we are the recipients of the greatest rescue story that's ever been told of God coming near, becoming like us.

32:39.042 --> 32:42.966
so that we could experience life with Him today and forever.

32:44.668 --> 32:45.108
Let's pray.

32:50.674 --> 33:05.810
Heavenly Father, I thank You just that all these stories we see and that we watch and that we read, these stories of rescue and sacrifice and courage

33:07.842 --> 33:20.041
Lord, that they are echoes of the greatest story, where a rescuer entered the world for us in a way that we didn't expect.

33:22.324 --> 33:33.682
God, as we sing these Christmas songs and as we reflect on this story, help us just be grateful that you saw us in our need.

33:37.922 --> 33:38.903
Lord, that you made a way.

33:40.525 --> 33:42.907
Guys, we think about Jesus as the Savior.

33:44.569 --> 33:54.400
God, I pray that we can trust in that reality, either for the first time or for the hundredth time today.

33:56.462 --> 34:02.249
And we can see how much of a blessing it is that we can know you and be known by you as well.

34:04.391 --> 34:07.154
In Jesus' name that we pray, amen.

